cs.CV, cs.AI, cs.LG, cs.RO, cs.MM

This paper is about object detection, which is a subfield of computer vision (cs.CV). The proposed method involves optimizing the point-guided approach in anchor-based object detection, which requires machine learning techniques (cs.AI) and optimization algorithms (cs.LG). The paper also mentions the use of feature pyramid networks (FPN) and the evaluation on the COCO dataset, which are relevant to robotics (cs.RO) and multimedia (cs.MM) respectively.
